The paper deals with the estimation of tilt angles for a multibody robot, which is a common problem in robotics and control systems. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of sensors and signal processing, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of inertial measurements and kinematic coupling suggests the involvement of machine learning and optimization techniques, which are covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper may involve image processing and computer vision techniques for simulation purposes, which is covered by cs.CV (Computer Vision).
